    catalogueProtectionTitle: 'Protection - Gender and Inclusion',
    catalogueProtectionCapacityText: 'Operation dependent.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyText1: 'PGI delegates are deployed to address specific protection, gender and inclusion issues affecting women, men, girls and boys (including elderly and persons with disabilities) during crises and build local protection capacities.\n\nMainstreaming',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyText2: 'Standalone',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem1: 'Monitor and support sex- age and disability data-collection to define people selection criteria and targeting.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem2: 'Provide technical advice to other teams on PGI mainstreaming (IFRC Minimum Standards for Protection, Gender and Inclusion; All Under One Roof Disability Inclusive Shelter and Settlements in Emergencies).',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem3: 'Support sectors in meeting accessibility standards in infrastructure and environment, information and communications.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem4: 'Provide technical monitoring of programmes using the Minimum Standard Monitoring Template.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem5: 'Provide advice to Head of Operations on ensuring implementation of Child Protection. Prevention of Sexual Exploitation and Abuse and reporting mechanisms.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem6: 'Roll out the Protection Incident Monitoring Reporting.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem7: 'Conduct PGI assessment and analysis.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem8: 'Requisition and deliver Dignity Kits.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem9: 'Establish DAPS Houses in line with DAPS House SOPs and quality standards.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem10: 'Train volunteers and staff in specialised services.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem11: 'Map and share SGBV and CP referral pathways ensuring the response meets Survivor Centered Approach standards.',
    catalogueProtectionEmergencyListItem12: 'Coordination with relevant ministries and other organization (representation in protection cluster and sub-clusters).',
    catalogueProtectionDesignedText: 'Designed for the provision of support to NS in PGI mainstreaming (all sectors) and initiating or augmenting standalone activities in communities affected by acute crises such as:',
    catalogueProtectionDesignedListItem1: 'Population movement.',
    catalogueProtectionDesignedListItem2: 'Natural disaster(s).',
    catalogueProtectionDesignedListItem3: 'Public health emergency.',
    catalogueProtectionPersonnelTotal: '1-2+ people.',
    catalogueProtectionPersonnelCompoistion: 'Typically deployed team includes one to two PGI delegates. Team can be expanded based on scale of the needs.',
    catalogueProtectionStandardCompText: 'PGI human capacity and tools needed to carry out needs assessments to identify at-risk groups and protection risks; support National Society to enhance dignity, access, participation and safety of affected individuals within the response; coordinating closely with relevant ministries and other humanitarian actors including representation in protection cluster and its sub-clusters, SGBV and child protection referrals, and setting up (standardized) Dignity Houses and/or safe spaces for vulnerable groups, as required.',
    catalogueEpoaTitle: 'Emergency Plan of Action (EPoA) Monitoring & Evaluation Plan',
    catalogueEpoaCapacityText: 'When a disaster or crisis occurs, the global surge request technical PMER support, which is mobilised by PMER Geneva and Regions. Experienced PMER personnel are contacted, identified and mobilised through the wider PMER network of IFRC and National Society contacts, based on operational need. It is recommended PMER is deployed in the early days or the response, alongside IM and CEA, to ensure strong planning and set up monitoring and reporting mechanisms (quality programming).',
    catalogueEpoaEmergencyListItem1: 'Development and coordination of the EPOA based on info gathered from needs assessment and field data gathering from technical teams.',
    catalogueEpoaEmergencyListItem2: 'Design of the M&E plan and setting up of data collection methods/processes and ongoing support to operational monitoring.',
    catalogueEpoaEmergencyListItem3: 'Supporting and ensuring the delivery of institutional and specific donor reporting requirements and standards.',
    catalogueEpoaDesignedText: 'Designed for the provision of support for all planning, monitoring and reporting functions to ensure the quality of the operation. These functions are essential for all emergency operations and should be considered core and the deployed personnel will also support the development of necessary planning, monitoring and reporting tools, processes and capacity building.',
    catalogueEpoaPersonnelText: 'See technical competencies and role profiles for: PMER Coordinator and PMER Delegate.',
    catalogueEpoaSpecifiationCost: 'Cost standard delegate and NSs staffing costs (IFRC or NS provision of staff).  Profiles include trained and experienced PMER personnel from IFRC and NSs, preference to staff with IFRC systems experience or NS with min experience with IFRC.',
    catalogueEpoaSpecifiationNationalSocieties: 'Multiple.',
    catalogueEpoaAdditionalNoteText: 'Close link between work of PMER staff and the IM and CEA teams.',
    catalogueRteTitle: 'Real Time Evaluation (RTE) and guidance',
    catalogueRteCapacityText: 'RTE trained evaluators tagged on global surge roster.',
    catalogueRteEmergencyText: 'Setting up and delivery a quality real-time or other evaluation of the operation, in line with the requirements of the IFRC’s M&E Framework and the criteria for holding a RTE (scale, scope, value and complexity of an operation).',
    catalogueRteDesignedText: 'RTEs and other evaluations are designed to assess, analyse and report back on the progress and quality of the operational delivery to affected populations and to help inform operational management decision-making and the future roll out of the response.',
    catalogueRtePersonnelText: 'RTE team leader externally recruited consultant. RTE team members identified from within the wider IFRC (Sect and NSs).',
    catalogueRteSpecifiationCost: 'Fees for the external consultant team leader. Mission costs for RCRC team members.',
    catalogueRteSpecifiationNationalSocieties: 'Multiple (plus external team leader).',
    catalogueRteAdditionalNoteText: 'RTEs are set up for all major operations meeting the relevant criteria (scale, scope, value and complexity - see RTE guidance).',
    catalogueReliefTitle: 'ERU Relief',
    catalogueReliefCapacityText: 'To support the host National Society to support/update relief assessments, targeted people selection, targeted people registration and to assist in planning and set-up for food, cash based interventions and household items (including emergency shelter material distributions), as well as produce relief distribution statistics and reports.',
    catalogueReliefEmergencyText1: 'The capacity of a deployed Relief ERU depends of support identified needs to carry out relief cycle activities:',
    catalogueReliefEmergencyText2: 'It could come through deployment of qualified personal without equipment to an equipped full team for a period of 4 months.',
